# Testing Rules

## Coverage Targets
- Unit: 70% minimum
- Critical paths: 90%+
- Security paths: 100%
- New code: 80%+

## Test Pyramid
- Many unit tests (fast)
- Some integration tests (medium)
- Few E2E tests (slow but valuable)

## Naming
- File: `<source>.test.ts`
- Describe: feature/class name
- It: behavior, not implementation
- "should X when Y"

## Structure
- Arrange: setup test data
- Act: execute behavior
- Assert: verify outcome
- Teardown: cleanup

## Database Tests
- Test DB per worker
- Truncate between tests (not migrate)
- Seed minimal data
- Use transactions where possible

## External Services
- Mock OpenAI/Anthropic in tests
- Mock S3 with localstack or memory
- Real Redis (fast enough)
- Real Postgres (test DB)

## E2E
- Critical user journeys only
- Run on PR + nightly
- Headed in dev, headless in CI
- Video on failure

## Security Tests
- Auth bypass attempts
- Tenant isolation tests
- Input validation
- Rate limit tests
- Sandbox escape (manual)

## CI
- Lint
- Type check
- Unit + integration on every PR
- E2E on main branch
- Security scan weekly